**Where:** `<core pipeline module path>`
**What:** A single public function (`<run_pipeline>` or whatever you
call it) that drives:

```
input
  → <Layer 1>.parse(input)             # returns <CORE_ABSTRACTION>
  → apply transforms (zero or more)
  → validate against schema + capability matrix
  → <Layer N>.render(<CORE_ABSTRACTION>) # returns output
```

**Critical invariant:** the signatures of pipeline-stage functions in
`<core pipeline module>` **must never change**.  External callers and
tests depend on the exact shape.  Later phases add NEW public
functions (e.g. `<plan_with_deploy>`); existing stages stay frozen.

